This paper deals with the computational complexity of a variant of Exact Cover, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of random instances of the problem, which suggests the involvement of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of an adiabatic quantum algorithm, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses the method of differential equations, which is a technique used in cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
